The paper deals with complexity theory, specifically the border rank of tensors and its implications for Strassen's laser method for matrix multiplication. This suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and systems and control (cs.SY) in its discussion of Kronecker powers of tensors and their properties.
